Used the NSL KDD Dataset for training that has the following Intrusions : 
1) Denial of Service (DoS)
2) Probe
3) User To Root (U2R) 
4) Remote to Local (R2L) 

This has to be noted that, knowledge of this information does not make it a supervided Learning Model. PCA script is an unsupervised anomaly detector. 
It does not read or use these attack labels during the training phase.
It only looks at the numerical features (duration, bytes, counts, rates) to learn the statistical pattern of "normal" traffic.
It calculates a reconstruction error threshold based on this "normal" pattern.

